<subSubSection id="36986DB9FF89E358FF5FFF0D8392DA3A" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7E3D3E32FF89E358FF5FFF0D8392DA3A" blockId="13.[151,1437,150,2013]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="4CF6E220FF89E358FF5FFF0D8021DBEE" bold="true" box="[199,314,150,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(only known from workers). Comparatively medium to large (TL 
<quantity id="B97A93D7FF89E358FBB8FF0D85DCDBEF" box="[1056,1223,150,177]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.07" metricValueMax="7.59" metricValueMin="6.55" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="7.07" valueMax="7.59" valueMin="6.55">6.55–7.59 mm</quantity>
); color light brown to dark brown; densely sculptured, rugose to areolar-rugose, procoxae and gaster foveate; petiole tubuliform, without projected node; mandibles triangular, long and pedunculate with twelve teeth on each masticatory margin; clypeomandibular space ample; labrum cuneiform, bilobed apically, lobes separated by a narrow cleft; pilosity consisting of a basal layer of flat and spatulate to subplumose decumbent curved hairs for most of their length, and another layer of long erect and clavate hairs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="36986DB9FF89E35BFF5FFEF58327DC50" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
